Got it!

00:00:52.969 --> 00:00:54.387 position:50% align:center
Step back when receiving!

00:01:02.437 --> 00:01:05.482 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA] We could shut the
PTA up by winning for once.

00:01:06.274 --> 00:01:08.568 position:50% align:center
It's Sota's fault
for not showing up.

00:01:08.651 --> 00:01:10.862 position:50% align:center
I didn't do anything wrong.

00:01:10.945 --> 00:01:12.781 position:50% align:center
Not a damn thing.

00:01:14.949 --> 00:01:17.243 position:50% align:center
We're right in the
middle of a match here.

00:01:17.327 --> 00:01:21.790 position:50% align:center
The hospital? Are you
sure it's Yoshino Sota?

00:01:21.873 --> 00:01:23.124 position:50% align:center
They found him at home?

00:01:23.208 --> 00:01:25.085 position:50% align:center
He tried to...?

00:03:14.027 --> 00:03:16.696 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
Chika! Wait up!

00:03:16.780 --> 00:03:17.530 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA]
Yuni.

00:03:17.614 --> 00:03:19.783 position:50% align:center
[pants]

00:03:19.866 --> 00:03:21.409 position:50% align:center
So, you're moving to Tokyo?

00:03:21.493 --> 00:03:23.995 position:50% align:center
We're not gonna see
each other anymore!

00:03:24.079 --> 00:03:27.123 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA]
Yeah. But I promise--

00:03:27.207 --> 00:03:30.377 position:50% align:center
No matter what I'll
never forget you, Yuni!

00:03:30.460 --> 00:03:32.337 position:50% align:center
I promise, too! Don't worry!

00:03:32.420 --> 00:03:34.673 position:50% align:center
I won't forget you, either!

00:03:35.674 --> 00:03:40.595 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA] I wish we could
have stayed together forever.

00:03:40.679 --> 00:03:42.597 position:50% align:center
Goodbye, Yuni.

00:03:50.647 --> 00:03:52.023 position:50% align:center
[ITOKO]
Guess what I heard.

00:03:52.107 --> 00:03:54.526 position:50% align:center
The transfer student's
gonna be late.

00:03:54.609 --> 00:03:56.319 position:50% align:center
I wonder if he's hot.

00:03:56.403 --> 00:03:58.405 position:50% align:center
Please tell me he's hot.

00:03:58.488 --> 00:04:00.407 position:50% align:center
Rest assured, he's average.

00:04:00.490 --> 00:04:01.741 position:50% align:center
Maybe even below so.

00:04:01.825 --> 00:04:03.743 position:50% align:center
Stop me if I'm wrong,
but last time you saw him

00:04:03.827 --> 00:04:05.495 position:50% align:center
was back in kindergarten, right?

00:04:05.578 --> 00:04:07.580 position:50% align:center
There's no telling what
he's gonna look like now.

00:04:07.664 --> 00:04:09.249 position:50% align:center
Fine, then here's my best guess.

00:04:09.332 --> 00:04:12.127 position:50% align:center
I'm sure he's still a four-eyed
shrimp who sucks at sports.

00:04:12.210 --> 00:04:13.128 position:50% align:center
What's with you?

00:04:13.211 --> 00:04:14.754 position:50% align:center
Always pouting like a kid.

00:04:14.838 --> 00:04:16.798 position:50% align:center
Is 'lil baby Kuroba grumpy?

00:04:16.881 --> 00:04:18.174 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
Give it a rest!

00:04:18.258 --> 00:04:19.968 position:50% align:center
What are you?
My older sister?

00:04:20.051 --> 00:04:21.594 position:50% align:center
Go annoy your own class.

00:04:21.678 --> 00:04:25.724 position:50% align:center
Yeah, yeah.
I was leaving anyway.

00:04:25.807 --> 00:04:26.933 position:50% align:center
I'm wearing shorts underneath,

00:04:27.017 --> 00:04:29.352 position:50% align:center
so there's no point
trying to sneak a peek.

00:04:29.436 --> 00:04:30.812 position:50% align:center
There're not even cute ones.

00:04:30.895 --> 00:04:32.605 position:50% align:center
What're those made of, wool?

00:04:32.689 --> 00:04:33.648 position:50% align:center
The school's heated.

00:04:33.732 --> 00:04:35.567 position:50% align:center
Why even wear them?

00:04:35.650 --> 00:04:37.318 position:50% align:center
Because, dork, they're stylish.

00:04:37.402 --> 00:04:40.405 position:50% align:center
No point trying to explain
the concept to you.

00:04:40.488 --> 00:04:41.740 position:50% align:center
You know what never gets old?

00:04:41.823 --> 00:04:43.742 position:50% align:center
All the different ways your
cousin gives you crap.

00:04:43.825 --> 00:04:45.702 position:50% align:center
Do me a favor
and shut your mouth.

00:04:45.785 --> 00:04:46.911 position:50% align:center
This transfer student--

00:04:46.995 --> 00:04:48.747 position:50% align:center
they're like a childhood
friend of yours?

00:04:48.830 --> 00:04:49.956 position:50% align:center
Back from kindergarten.

00:04:50.040 --> 00:04:52.334 position:50% align:center
That long?
Reunited at last, huh?

00:04:52.417 --> 00:04:56.671 position:50% align:center
Seriously? Please.
He's just a dude.

00:04:56.755 --> 00:05:00.091 position:50% align:center
To be honest,
I was pretty excited.

00:05:01.801 --> 00:05:03.094 position:50% align:center
What's Chika's problem?

00:05:03.178 --> 00:05:05.722 position:50% align:center
The guy finished moving back
during the winter break.

00:05:05.805 --> 00:05:08.683 position:50% align:center
He didn't even
stop by to see me once.

00:05:23.865 --> 00:05:25.367 position:50% align:center
Chika!

00:05:38.463 --> 00:05:44.052 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA] Huh?
Maybe he didn't recognize me?

00:05:46.054 --> 00:05:48.890 position:50% align:center
[TEACHER] This is
Haijima Kimichika from Tokyo.

00:05:48.973 --> 00:05:50.850 position:50% align:center
I understand his
grandfather lives here,

00:05:50.934 --> 00:05:52.227 position:50% align:center
and he resided in Suzumu

00:05:52.310 --> 00:05:55.271 position:50% align:center
until he was in kindergarten
and had to move away.

00:05:55.355 --> 00:05:56.773 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
I'll ignore you.

00:05:56.856 --> 00:05:58.358 position:50% align:center
--[TEACHER] Kuroba.
--Huh? What?

00:05:58.441 --> 00:05:59.984 position:50% align:center
Apparently,
Haijima played volleyball

00:06:00.068 --> 00:06:02.696 position:50% align:center
at his previous school and
has decided to join our team.

00:06:02.779 --> 00:06:04.489 position:50% align:center
Since he's a
brand-new student here,

00:06:04.572 --> 00:06:05.657 position:50% align:center
I trust you'll make sure

00:06:05.740 --> 00:06:07.492 position:50% align:center
to show him around
our school, won't you?

00:06:07.575 --> 00:06:08.785 position:50% align:center
Speaking of which,

00:06:08.868 --> 00:06:11.663 position:50% align:center
why don't you take a seat
in front of Kuroba?

00:06:16.001 --> 00:06:17.043 position:50% align:center
What position?

00:06:17.127 --> 00:06:18.086 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:06:18.169 --> 00:06:20.171 position:50% align:center
Yeah? Well?
You do play volleyball?

00:06:20.255 --> 00:06:22.382 position:50% align:center
You're talking about
my position on the team.

00:06:22.465 --> 00:06:23.842 position:50% align:center
The truth is,

00:06:23.925 --> 00:06:26.344 position:50% align:center
I don't really have like a
designated spot or anything.

00:06:26.428 --> 00:06:28.013 position:50% align:center
I'm not sure I understand.

00:06:28.096 --> 00:06:30.140 position:50% align:center
You have a system
to decide during matches?

00:06:30.223 --> 00:06:31.391 position:50% align:center
You're gonna laugh,

00:06:31.474 --> 00:06:33.101 position:50% align:center
but I've never played
an actual match before

00:06:33.184 --> 00:06:35.061 position:50% align:center
and our practices
are kinda whenever.

00:06:35.145 --> 00:06:36.980 position:50% align:center
Full disclosure,
most of the guys on the team

00:06:37.063 --> 00:06:39.149 position:50% align:center
just needed some
sort of club to join.

00:06:39.232 --> 00:06:40.942 position:50% align:center
Oh, right. Joining a club.

00:06:41.026 --> 00:06:42.527 position:50% align:center
It's sort of
required by the school,

00:06:42.610 --> 00:06:44.696 position:50% align:center
but I guess you
wouldn't have known that.

00:06:45.613 --> 00:06:46.948 position:50% align:center
Hey, did your last
school have some kind of

00:06:47.032 --> 00:06:51.119 position:50% align:center
super outstanding volleyball
team or something?

00:06:51.202 --> 00:06:53.329 position:50% align:center
You're a waste of centimeters.

00:06:53.413 --> 00:06:55.415 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
Wha...? A waste?

00:06:55.498 --> 00:06:57.876 position:50% align:center
What's going on with him?

00:06:58.918 --> 00:07:01.546 position:50% align:center
[YORIMICHI]
Chika? Wait. Kimichika?

00:07:01.629 --> 00:07:03.465 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I remember that kid.

00:07:03.548 --> 00:07:06.760 position:50% align:center
Good to know, because
if you do, he must be real.

00:07:06.843 --> 00:07:09.346 position:50% align:center
Not some figment
of my imagination.

00:07:09.429 --> 00:07:11.514 position:50% align:center
You didn't seriously
think he was a ghost?

00:07:11.598 --> 00:07:13.975 position:50% align:center
I swear, you're
as stupid as ever.

00:07:14.059 --> 00:07:17.604 position:50% align:center
If you're so smart, then tell me
the reason he moved to Tokyo?

00:07:17.687 --> 00:07:19.105 position:50% align:center
Or do you actually know?

00:07:19.189 --> 00:07:21.399 position:50% align:center
'Cause of his mom dying and all.

00:07:21.483 --> 00:07:23.360 position:50% align:center
I can still remember
the geezer all dressed up

00:07:23.443 --> 00:07:26.029 position:50% align:center
on the day of her funeral.

00:07:26.112 --> 00:07:29.824 position:50% align:center
As for his pops, he was
originally from Tokyo.

00:07:29.908 --> 00:07:31.326 position:50% align:center
Kinda makes me wonder why

00:07:31.409 --> 00:07:35.914 position:50% align:center
he ended up coming
back to this place.

00:07:35.997 --> 00:07:37.791 position:50% align:center
Man, like I know.

00:07:37.874 --> 00:07:39.125 position:50% align:center
Ask him yourself.

00:07:39.209 --> 00:07:42.379 position:50% align:center
If I could, do you think
I'd be in this mess?

00:07:42.462 --> 00:07:46.091 position:50% align:center
He's got this barrier
around right now.

00:07:46.174 --> 00:07:49.636 position:50% align:center
Hey, um, I'm not a waste
of centimeters, am I?

00:07:49.719 --> 00:07:51.513 position:50% align:center
[YORIMICHI]
I'm the wrong person to ask.

00:07:51.596 --> 00:07:54.891 position:50% align:center
As a fellow pointlessly tall
person, I can't be objective.

00:07:54.974 --> 00:07:57.602 position:50% align:center
Still, you ain't got
nothin' on my height.

00:07:57.686 --> 00:07:58.436 position:50% align:center
Yeah?

00:07:58.520 --> 00:07:59.938 position:50% align:center
No need to go and brag.

00:08:00.021 --> 00:08:01.648 position:50% align:center
--[YORIMICHI] Here.
--[ITOKO] You there, Yuni?

00:08:01.731 --> 00:08:03.566 position:50% align:center
Auntie says
it's time for dinner.

00:08:03.650 --> 00:08:05.610 position:50% align:center
Get your butt home.

00:08:06.820 --> 00:08:08.154 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
Hold on a sec.

00:08:08.238 --> 00:08:10.573 position:50% align:center
How did Itoko know
I was with you?

00:08:10.657 --> 00:08:12.992 position:50% align:center
[YORIMICHI]
Seriously, you're such an idiot.

00:08:13.076 --> 00:08:14.536 position:50% align:center
Why's that?

00:08:16.830 --> 00:08:18.289 position:50% align:center
Hello, Kuroba.

00:08:18.373 --> 00:08:20.709 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
Hey, Chika! I mean, Haijima.

00:08:20.792 --> 00:08:22.293 position:50% align:center
Why're you out so late?

00:08:22.377 --> 00:08:23.628 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA]
I had club.

00:08:23.712 --> 00:08:26.715 position:50% align:center
As in, like, volleyball?

00:08:26.798 --> 00:08:28.008 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA]
Practice was today.

00:08:28.091 --> 00:08:30.427 position:50% align:center
Sure, but no one else was there.

00:08:30.510 --> 00:08:32.012 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA]
No.

00:08:32.095 --> 00:08:33.680 position:50% align:center
You practiced by yourself?

00:08:33.763 --> 00:08:35.056 position:50% align:center
That's right.

00:08:35.140 --> 00:08:37.684 position:50% align:center
[YORIMICHI]
Hey. This is Chika, huh?

00:08:37.767 --> 00:08:40.020 position:50% align:center
You were a runt
last time I saw you.

00:08:40.103 --> 00:08:42.564 position:50% align:center
Dude's almost
as tall as you, Yuni.

00:08:42.647 --> 00:08:45.525 position:50% align:center
This is Yori. You've met before.

00:08:45.608 --> 00:08:48.445 position:50% align:center
He's my cousin who used
play <i>shogi</i> at Gramp's place.

00:08:48.528 --> 00:08:51.239 position:50% align:center
I remember him. So what?

00:08:55.201 --> 00:09:00.040 position:50% align:center
Just so you know, you're wasting
your height and your life.

00:09:00.123 --> 00:09:02.083 position:50% align:center
[YORIMICHI]
What's that supposed to mean?

00:09:02.167 --> 00:09:03.209 position:50% align:center
You think you're going around

00:09:03.293 --> 00:09:05.295 position:50% align:center
doin' something amazing
with yours, huh?

00:09:05.378 --> 00:09:07.672 position:50% align:center
Compared to you two, yeah.

00:09:09.466 --> 00:09:10.842 position:50% align:center
What's his problem?

00:09:10.925 --> 00:09:13.428 position:50% align:center
Height's not the only thing
that's changed about him.

00:09:13.511 --> 00:09:15.263 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
He acts the same way at school.

00:09:15.347 --> 00:09:17.057 position:50% align:center
Guy's a loner.

00:09:19.768 --> 00:09:22.187 position:50% align:center
[BASKETBALL CAPTAIN]
Come on! Next up! Go!

00:09:58.098 --> 00:09:59.766 position:50% align:center
That's a heckuva spike serve.

00:09:59.849 --> 00:10:01.685 position:50% align:center
So awesome.

00:10:01.768 --> 00:10:03.311 position:50% align:center
[BASKETBALL CAPTAIN]
Hey, Transfer Student.

00:10:03.395 --> 00:10:04.979 position:50% align:center
By yourself again, I see.

00:10:05.063 --> 00:10:06.648 position:50% align:center
Don't know if
you've noticed or not,

00:10:06.731 --> 00:10:09.317 position:50% align:center
but we're kinda short
on space 'cause of you.

00:10:09.401 --> 00:10:11.444 position:50% align:center
Seeing how you
don't have a team,

00:10:11.528 --> 00:10:13.238 position:50% align:center
how 'bout practicing
in a corner?

00:10:13.321 --> 00:10:15.031 position:50% align:center
[BASKETBALL A]
We need to use the whole gym.

00:10:15.115 --> 00:10:17.033 position:50% align:center
Anything less,
we're missing out.

00:10:17.117 --> 00:10:19.160 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA] And my sport
requires half the gym.

00:10:19.244 --> 00:10:21.121 position:50% align:center
There're more of you, so what?

00:10:21.204 --> 00:10:23.331 position:50% align:center
If you don't have
enough room to practice

00:10:23.415 --> 00:10:25.291 position:50% align:center
then take it up
with your advisor.

00:10:25.375 --> 00:10:28.420 position:50% align:center
You just got here, and you act
like you run the school.

00:10:28.503 --> 00:10:33.550 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA] Yo. Now there're two
of us, so stop complaining.

00:10:33.633 --> 00:10:37.053 position:50% align:center
Um, sorry for
being late and stuff.

00:10:38.054 --> 00:10:39.806 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA]
What's your deal?

00:10:39.889 --> 00:10:41.933 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
Just sizing you up.

00:10:42.017 --> 00:10:43.226 position:50% align:center
After you had
the nerve to tell me

00:10:43.309 --> 00:10:45.353 position:50% align:center
I was wastin' my life yesterday.

00:10:45.437 --> 00:10:46.980 position:50% align:center
I figured why
not stop by the gym

00:10:47.063 --> 00:10:49.107 position:50% align:center
and see what you
were doing with yours?

00:10:49.190 --> 00:10:50.400 position:50% align:center
And in case you were wondering,

00:10:50.483 --> 00:10:52.652 position:50% align:center
I didn't come here
to help you out, okay?

00:10:52.736 --> 00:10:54.362 position:50% align:center
It's not like you needed it.

00:10:54.446 --> 00:10:57.741 position:50% align:center
Still, one up against
20 isn't an even match.

00:10:57.824 --> 00:10:59.909 position:50% align:center
Not sure two against
20 will make that much

00:10:59.993 --> 00:11:01.703 position:50% align:center
of a difference in
the long run either.

00:11:01.786 --> 00:11:04.497 position:50% align:center
Do you have any idea
of how annoying you are?

00:11:04.581 --> 00:11:05.874 position:50% align:center
For real though,
is it any wonder

00:11:05.957 --> 00:11:09.294 position:50% align:center
you don't have
a single friend at school?

00:11:12.839 --> 00:11:14.716 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA] By the way,
those spike serves earlier

00:11:14.799 --> 00:11:16.593 position:50% align:center
were looking pretty awesome.

00:11:16.676 --> 00:11:19.971 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA] I need to get better,
or I can't use them in matches.

00:11:20.055 --> 00:11:23.641 position:50% align:center
Ah-ha, so that's why you were
here working on your serves.

00:11:23.725 --> 00:11:27.437 position:50% align:center
No, that's all I can do
while practicing alone.

00:11:30.065 --> 00:11:33.693 position:50% align:center
I don't have my tracksuit, but I
suppose I could do some drills.

00:11:33.777 --> 00:11:37.030 position:50% align:center
Besides, it's not like
I made plans with Yori today.

00:11:37.113 --> 00:11:39.824 position:50% align:center
Fair warning to you though,
I'm still pretty sucky,

00:11:39.908 --> 00:11:41.826 position:50% align:center
so I might not be much help.

00:11:41.910 --> 00:11:44.245 position:50% align:center
You feel you're better off
on your own, I'll go.

00:11:44.329 --> 00:11:45.830 position:50% align:center
Cool?

00:11:48.249 --> 00:11:49.876 position:50% align:center
What's with that look dude?

00:11:49.959 --> 00:11:51.920 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA] Hang on.
I'll put in my contacts.

00:11:52.003 --> 00:11:53.755 position:50% align:center
Uh... Why?

00:11:53.838 --> 00:11:56.174 position:50% align:center
