00:12:39.592 --> 00:12:42.721 position:50% align:center
You and I have pretty different
ideas of warming up.

00:12:42.804 --> 00:12:45.390 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA] Kuroba,
how tall are you right now?

00:12:45.473 --> 00:12:48.143 position:50% align:center
Huh? Hundred
seventy-three centimeters.

00:12:48.226 --> 00:12:50.228 position:50% align:center
When did you last check that?

00:12:50.311 --> 00:12:53.982 position:50% align:center
Hmm... Some time back
in the fall I guess.

00:12:57.318 --> 00:12:59.029 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA]
You're a 175.

00:12:59.112 --> 00:13:02.073 position:50% align:center
Hey, tacked on two centimeters.

00:13:02.157 --> 00:13:03.533 position:50% align:center
Now measure me.

00:13:05.410 --> 00:13:08.329 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
A 172.7.

00:13:08.413 --> 00:13:09.873 position:50% align:center
You're not that much taller.

00:13:09.956 --> 00:13:10.957 position:50% align:center
Two centimeters.

00:13:11.041 --> 00:13:13.043 position:50% align:center
Uh, 2.3, actually.

00:13:13.126 --> 00:13:14.711 position:50% align:center
Still, you're a setter, right?

00:13:14.794 --> 00:13:17.547 position:50% align:center
Not like you have to worry
that much about height.

00:13:17.630 --> 00:13:20.508 position:50% align:center
Let me tell you
about a tall setter.

00:13:20.592 --> 00:13:22.844 position:50% align:center
A player on the
national team named Abe.

00:13:22.927 --> 00:13:25.430 position:50% align:center
He's a setter, a 191.

00:13:25.513 --> 00:13:28.308 position:50% align:center
The taller you are, the higher
all your sets will be.

00:13:28.391 --> 00:13:30.727 position:50% align:center
That's why Abe's a master
at the front of the net.

00:13:30.810 --> 00:13:33.730 position:50% align:center
Plus, he's ambidextrous
with sweet left-hand dumps.

00:13:33.813 --> 00:13:35.106 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
Oh, yeah.

00:13:35.190 --> 00:13:38.234 position:50% align:center
So, I noticed earlier,
you were using both hands, too.

00:13:38.318 --> 00:13:39.402 position:50% align:center
You're ambidextrous?

00:13:39.486 --> 00:13:41.237 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA]
No, but I trained myself.

00:13:41.321 --> 00:13:43.156 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
How would you even start?

00:13:43.239 --> 00:13:45.241 position:50% align:center
That blows my mind.

00:13:46.576 --> 00:13:48.078 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
Ryo? What's up?

00:13:48.161 --> 00:13:49.287 position:50% align:center
Not much.

00:13:49.371 --> 00:13:51.247 position:50% align:center
Yeah, so, uh, I heard
the volleyball club

00:13:51.331 --> 00:13:53.375 position:50% align:center
was meeting up here
for practice today.

00:13:53.458 --> 00:13:54.376 position:50% align:center
It's only us, but--

00:13:54.459 --> 00:13:55.835 position:50% align:center
Yeah, that's right.

00:13:55.919 --> 00:13:59.339 position:50% align:center
Now that you're here we can
get a serious practice in.

00:14:55.603 --> 00:14:57.188 position:50% align:center
Hey, Kuroba.

00:14:57.272 --> 00:14:58.898 position:50% align:center
During practice games,
look at the block

00:14:58.982 --> 00:15:01.401 position:50% align:center
before choosing
a cross or a straight.

00:15:01.484 --> 00:15:03.403 position:50% align:center
Lemme see if
I can remember this.

00:15:03.486 --> 00:15:04.654 position:50% align:center
So, a straight attack is

00:15:04.738 --> 00:15:06.406 position:50% align:center
when you hit the ball
right through the court,

00:15:06.489 --> 00:15:08.825 position:50% align:center
while a cross is one
that's more on the outside.

00:15:08.908 --> 00:15:10.827 position:50% align:center
Other way, genius.

00:15:10.910 --> 00:15:13.455 position:50% align:center
A spike you hit diagonally
through the court is a cross

00:15:13.538 --> 00:15:14.914 position:50% align:center
while a hit that's parallel

00:15:14.998 --> 00:15:17.250 position:50% align:center
to the sideline is
called a straight.

00:15:17.334 --> 00:15:19.085 position:50% align:center
Whenever you're up
front by the net,

00:15:19.169 --> 00:15:20.587 position:50% align:center
you've got a habit
of taking a step

00:15:20.670 --> 00:15:22.589 position:50% align:center
while facing towards the middle.

00:15:22.672 --> 00:15:24.966 position:50% align:center
If you just hit it naturally,
that'd be a cross

00:15:25.050 --> 00:15:26.593 position:50% align:center
but if you wanted
to aim for the outside,

00:15:26.676 --> 00:15:28.595 position:50% align:center
then it would be
a straight, 'kay?

00:15:28.678 --> 00:15:29.888 position:50% align:center
That's real confusing.

00:15:29.971 --> 00:15:32.265 position:50% align:center
It's beginner level stuff,
but whatever.

00:15:32.349 --> 00:15:34.434 position:50% align:center
We'll do drills
so you don't forget.

00:15:34.517 --> 00:15:36.227 position:50% align:center
Afraid you'd say that.

00:15:37.562 --> 00:15:39.397 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA]
Mentally you don't get it,

00:15:39.481 --> 00:15:41.816 position:50% align:center
but you know how
to get around blocks.

00:15:41.900 --> 00:15:43.860 position:50% align:center
The way you use your upper body,

00:15:43.943 --> 00:15:45.570 position:50% align:center
the flexibility
of your shoulders,

00:15:45.653 --> 00:15:47.364 position:50% align:center
how you stay in the air.

00:15:47.447 --> 00:15:48.948 position:50% align:center
Don't worry, though.

00:15:49.032 --> 00:15:51.743 position:50% align:center
While those are the only natural
talents you have for the sport,

00:15:51.826 --> 00:15:54.329 position:50% align:center
in time, you'll get better.

00:15:54.412 --> 00:15:56.247 position:50% align:center
But only if you put in the work.

00:15:56.331 --> 00:15:58.541 position:50% align:center
Getting taller
wouldn't hurt, either.

00:15:58.625 --> 00:16:00.168 position:50% align:center
Thanks for the
first part at least.

00:16:00.251 --> 00:16:01.294 position:50% align:center
What's your deal?

00:16:01.378 --> 00:16:02.837 position:50% align:center
Was something I said incorrect?

00:16:02.921 --> 00:16:05.382 position:50% align:center
You're always acting like you're
better than everybody else,

00:16:05.465 --> 00:16:07.842 position:50% align:center
so hearing you offering me
a legitimate compliment

00:16:07.926 --> 00:16:10.387 position:50% align:center
is a little disconcerting,
no offense intended.

00:16:10.470 --> 00:16:11.971 position:50% align:center
Of course I'm going to
acknowledge something

00:16:12.055 --> 00:16:14.641 position:50% align:center
that deserves to be
acknowledged.

00:16:14.724 --> 00:16:17.644 position:50% align:center
Even if I ended up
being great at volleyball,

00:16:17.727 --> 00:16:20.021 position:50% align:center
I'd still be unpopular.

00:16:22.524 --> 00:16:25.193 position:50% align:center
So, what's the verdict
on high school?

00:16:25.276 --> 00:16:26.695 position:50% align:center
Are you gonna go here?

00:16:26.778 --> 00:16:29.072 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA]
For now, that's the plan, but...

00:16:29.155 --> 00:16:30.198 position:50% align:center
There's more?

00:16:30.281 --> 00:16:32.242 position:50% align:center
It's not like you
have to stay, right?

00:16:32.325 --> 00:16:33.785 position:50% align:center
More importantly,

00:16:33.868 --> 00:16:36.204 position:50% align:center
we've got first-year
students joining in April.

00:16:36.287 --> 00:16:37.872 position:50% align:center
Yeah. You're right, but

00:16:37.956 --> 00:16:40.000 position:50% align:center
you shouldn't get
your hopes up too much.

00:16:40.083 --> 00:16:42.544 position:50% align:center
We can probably snag one or two.

00:16:42.627 --> 00:16:44.838 position:50% align:center
If we get more,
I want to compete.

00:16:44.921 --> 00:16:46.214 position:50% align:center
I don't know whether
the schedule here

00:16:46.297 --> 00:16:48.008 position:50% align:center
is like most other places,

00:16:48.091 --> 00:16:49.175 position:50% align:center
but before the nationals,

00:16:49.259 --> 00:16:51.594 position:50% align:center
there should be a
prefectural tournament.

00:16:51.678 --> 00:16:53.638 position:50% align:center
Not to be a downer,
but even if we entered,

00:16:53.722 --> 00:16:55.849 position:50% align:center
I doubt we'd make it that far.

00:16:55.932 --> 00:16:58.560 position:50% align:center
Volleyball's not fun
if you're not competing.

00:16:58.643 --> 00:17:01.021 position:50% align:center
That's the entire purpose.

00:17:01.104 --> 00:17:03.398 position:50% align:center
I'll make sure we're
presentable by summer.

00:17:03.481 --> 00:17:05.316 position:50% align:center
Keep showing up to practice.

00:17:05.400 --> 00:17:07.444 position:50% align:center
I'll figure out the rest.

00:17:07.527 --> 00:17:08.820 position:50% align:center
Welp, good luck.

00:17:08.903 --> 00:17:10.530 position:50% align:center
But don't we have
to have an advisor

00:17:10.613 --> 00:17:12.240 position:50% align:center
before we enter a tournament?

00:17:12.323 --> 00:17:13.950 position:50% align:center
Why don't we ask around
at school tomorrow?

00:17:14.034 --> 00:17:15.118 position:50% align:center
[FRIEND A]
Sup.

00:17:15.201 --> 00:17:17.454 position:50% align:center
Well, if it isn't mister
moneybags himself.

00:17:17.537 --> 00:17:19.456 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
Heya. It's been a while.

00:17:19.539 --> 00:17:21.833 position:50% align:center
What's up, Yori?

00:17:21.916 --> 00:17:22.751 position:50% align:center
What's going on?

00:17:22.834 --> 00:17:24.461 position:50% align:center
Why're you guys back in town?

00:17:24.544 --> 00:17:26.588 position:50% align:center
Out of college
for spring break, man.

00:17:26.671 --> 00:17:27.547 position:50% align:center
Rich Boy!

00:17:27.630 --> 00:17:29.507 position:50% align:center
Lend us some cash, wouldya?

00:17:29.591 --> 00:17:30.550 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
Uh...

00:17:30.633 --> 00:17:32.260 position:50% align:center
I've only got
some pocket change.

00:17:32.344 --> 00:17:34.387 position:50% align:center
I don't carry much since
I leave my bag lying around

00:17:34.471 --> 00:17:35.764 position:50% align:center
while I'm in club.

00:17:35.847 --> 00:17:36.806 position:50% align:center
[FRIEND B]
You're in a club?

00:17:36.890 --> 00:17:38.058 position:50% align:center
[FRIEND A]
Yeah, so we heard.

00:17:38.141 --> 00:17:40.268 position:50% align:center
Yorimichi mentioned
somethin' 'bout that.

00:17:40.352 --> 00:17:42.062 position:50% align:center
Volleyball, I think he told us.

00:17:42.145 --> 00:17:43.688 position:50% align:center
Well, come on,
let's see some moves.

00:17:43.772 --> 00:17:45.774 position:50% align:center
How about showin' us
a receive, bro?

00:17:45.857 --> 00:17:47.734 position:50% align:center
Y'know, I always forget
what those look like.

00:17:47.817 --> 00:17:49.486 position:50% align:center
Refresh my memory.

00:17:49.569 --> 00:17:52.238 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
I think it's sorta like this?

00:17:52.322 --> 00:17:53.907 position:50% align:center
[FRIEND A]
We got ourselves a natural here!

00:17:53.990 --> 00:17:55.367 position:50% align:center
[FRIEND B chuckles]
Looking real cool,

00:17:55.450 --> 00:17:57.285 position:50% align:center
like you're a legit
volleyball player.

00:17:57.369 --> 00:17:58.787 position:50% align:center
[laughter]

00:17:58.870 --> 00:18:00.246 position:50% align:center
--Haijima?
--Stop playing games

00:18:00.330 --> 00:18:02.499 position:50% align:center
and let's go. Waste of time.

00:18:02.582 --> 00:18:04.250 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
Could you stop pulling me first?

00:18:04.334 --> 00:18:07.170 position:50% align:center
It's only a game, don't forget.

00:18:08.546 --> 00:18:10.757 position:50% align:center
[YORIMICHI] Don't tell me
you're actually serious

00:18:10.840 --> 00:18:13.301 position:50% align:center
'bout joining this stupid jock.

00:18:13.385 --> 00:18:14.344 position:50% align:center
Come on.

00:18:14.427 --> 00:18:16.096 position:50% align:center
You're not mad at me,
are you, Yori?

00:18:16.179 --> 00:18:18.973 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry we haven't gotten
a chance to hang out recently,

00:18:19.057 --> 00:18:21.518 position:50% align:center
but we should totally
meet up during the break.

00:18:21.601 --> 00:18:23.269 position:50% align:center
We practice during spring break.

00:18:23.353 --> 00:18:26.064 position:50% align:center
We're not talkin' about
every day though, right?

00:18:26.147 --> 00:18:27.899 position:50% align:center
If we're going to enter
the summer tournament,

00:18:27.982 --> 00:18:29.859 position:50% align:center
I doubt even
that'll be enough time.

00:18:29.943 --> 00:18:31.736 position:50% align:center
Are you for real?

00:18:31.820 --> 00:18:33.530 position:50% align:center
[YORIMICHI]
Yuni.

00:18:33.613 --> 00:18:36.741 position:50% align:center
You realize, don't you, that
you're never gonna make it?

00:18:36.825 --> 00:18:41.037 position:50% align:center
Treat it like a game and you
won't make a fool of yourself.

00:18:41.121 --> 00:18:43.623 position:50% align:center
So what's it gonna be,
him or us?

00:18:43.707 --> 00:18:45.792 position:50% align:center
I ain't the type
to wait around for long.

00:18:45.875 --> 00:18:46.710 position:50% align:center
Hey, now.

00:18:46.793 --> 00:18:48.336 position:50% align:center
We're only kidding here, right?

00:18:48.420 --> 00:18:50.046 position:50% align:center
You're just as bad as he is.

00:18:50.130 --> 00:18:52.841 position:50% align:center
Man. Money sure
makes you popular.

00:18:52.924 --> 00:18:55.218 position:50% align:center
You turn around for a
minute and he replaces you.

00:18:55.301 --> 00:18:56.678 position:50% align:center
Some friend, huh?

00:18:56.761 --> 00:18:57.887 position:50% align:center
Come on.

00:18:57.971 --> 00:18:59.347 position:50% align:center
We're cousins.

00:18:59.431 --> 00:19:02.350 position:50% align:center
You know how I always dive
into new things all excited

00:19:02.434 --> 00:19:04.769 position:50% align:center
and then get bored
with them just as quickly.

00:19:04.853 --> 00:19:08.565 position:50% align:center
And sooner or later, I'll wind
up getting tired of volleyball.

00:19:08.648 --> 00:19:09.733 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:19:10.358 --> 00:19:11.901 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA]
Were you serious just now?

00:19:11.985 --> 00:19:15.363 position:50% align:center
[KUROBA]
Well, I... The thing is...

00:19:15.447 --> 00:19:16.865 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA]
Then go ahead and quit!

00:19:16.948 --> 00:19:19.200 position:50% align:center
Why're you taking
this from zero to a 100?

00:19:19.284 --> 00:19:21.411 position:50% align:center
I'm not letting you
ruin the tournament.

00:19:21.494 --> 00:19:22.704 position:50% align:center
And what does that mean?

00:19:22.787 --> 00:19:24.789 position:50% align:center
You'd only get in my way.

00:19:24.873 --> 00:19:26.708 position:50% align:center
I want to actually
play in matches!

00:19:26.791 --> 00:19:27.834 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:19:29.210 --> 00:19:30.462 position:50% align:center
Ha! Bingo.

00:19:30.545 --> 00:19:32.589 position:50% align:center
Showing your
true colors, at last.

00:19:32.672 --> 00:19:35.967 position:50% align:center
The genius setter from Meisei,
living up to his reputation.

00:19:36.051 --> 00:19:37.927 position:50% align:center
Always putting himself
before anyone else,

00:19:38.011 --> 00:19:40.055 position:50% align:center
especially his own teammates.

00:19:40.138 --> 00:19:41.222 position:50% align:center
I'm confused.

00:19:41.306 --> 00:19:43.308 position:50% align:center
What are you
talking about, Yori?

00:19:43.391 --> 00:19:46.686 position:50% align:center
[YORIMICHI] The reason
Chika came back to town.

00:19:46.770 --> 00:19:49.481 position:50% align:center
You said you wanted
to know, didn't you?

00:19:49.564 --> 00:19:52.317 position:50% align:center
So, I did some digging.

00:19:52.400 --> 00:19:53.610 position:50% align:center
You hear me?

00:19:53.693 --> 00:19:56.279 position:50% align:center
Everyone reaps what they sow,
you little punk.

00:19:56.363 --> 00:19:58.948 position:50% align:center
So don't go blaming
your problems on Yuni.

00:19:59.032 --> 00:20:01.701 position:50% align:center
--Yori, wait.
--Stay outta the way.

00:20:01.785 --> 00:20:04.829 position:50% align:center
I managed to get your old
school name from your gramps.

00:20:04.913 --> 00:20:07.791 position:50% align:center
Thought you could keep it
a secret from everyone, huh?

00:20:07.874 --> 00:20:11.211 position:50% align:center
I did a little snooping online
to see what I could find out

00:20:11.294 --> 00:20:13.296 position:50% align:center
and did I hit the jackpot!

00:20:13.380 --> 00:20:16.049 position:50% align:center
Page after page about
the volleyball prodigy

00:20:16.132 --> 00:20:18.885 position:50% align:center
who went to school there,
up until last year.

00:20:18.968 --> 00:20:21.346 position:50% align:center
Boy, do they hate you now.

00:20:23.098 --> 00:20:23.973 position:50% align:center
Yuni.

00:20:24.057 --> 00:20:25.433 position:50% align:center
Uh, yeah?

00:20:25.517 --> 00:20:26.976 position:50% align:center
I don't want you
to think this is just

00:20:27.060 --> 00:20:29.396 position:50% align:center
some personal
vendetta against Chika.

00:20:29.479 --> 00:20:31.606 position:50% align:center
Although he'd deserve that.

00:20:31.690 --> 00:20:33.733 position:50% align:center
We're doing this for you.

00:20:33.817 --> 00:20:37.278 position:50% align:center
I'm warning you, don't even
get involved with volleyball.

00:20:37.362 --> 00:20:38.780 position:50% align:center
But, why not?

00:20:38.863 --> 00:20:42.409 position:50% align:center
Because this loser here will
do whatever it takes to win.

00:20:42.492 --> 00:20:44.577 position:50% align:center
And I mean anything.

00:20:45.370 --> 00:20:46.454 position:50% align:center
[HAIJIMA]
Play the game right!

00:20:46.538 --> 00:20:48.915 position:50% align:center
You're on the left,
so receive the ball!

00:20:48.998 --> 00:20:50.625 position:50% align:center
Then you make sure
to get it to me!

00:20:50.709 --> 00:20:51.710 position:50% align:center
The setter!

00:20:51.793 --> 00:20:54.462 position:50% align:center
How many times
do I need to tell you?

00:20:54.546 --> 00:20:58.091 position:50% align:center
If you can't even do that right,
then what are you good for?

00:20:59.968 --> 00:21:01.469 position:50% align:center
[MEISEI COACH] You won't
be in the starting lineup

00:21:01.553 --> 00:21:02.929 position:50% align:center
for tomorrow's game.

00:21:03.013 --> 00:21:04.973 position:50% align:center
Hopefully, that'll diffuse
things with Yoshino

00:21:05.056 --> 00:21:09.060 position:50% align:center
and the rest of the team,
as well as the parents.

00:21:09.144 --> 00:21:10.645 position:50% align:center
The hospital?

00:21:10.729 --> 00:21:13.815 position:50% align:center
Are you sure it's Yoshino Sota?

00:21:13.898 --> 00:21:15.150 position:50% align:center
They found him at home?

00:21:15.233 --> 00:21:16.735 position:50% align:center
He tried to...?

00:21:17.986 --> 00:21:19.404 position:50% align:center
Wanna know the dirty truth?

00:21:19.487 --> 00:21:21.823 position:50% align:center
This jackass here,

00:21:21.906 --> 00:21:23.825 position:50% align:center
He pushed another
teammate over the edge

00:21:23.908 --> 00:21:25.410 position:50% align:center
for not listening to him.

00:21:25.493 --> 00:21:27.412 position:50% align:center
The kid tried to off himself.